Package: scLVM
Type: Package
Title: Dissecting heterogeneity in single-cell RNA-seq experiments.
Version: 0.99.1
Date: 2015-04-09
Author: Florian Buettner, Paolo Casale, Oliver Stegle
Maintainer:Florian Buettner <buettner@ebi.ac.uk>
Description: scLVM is a modelling framework for single-cell RNA-seq data that can be used to dissect the observed heterogeneity into different sources, thereby allowing for the correction of confounding sources of variation.
License: Apache-2.0
Depends: methods,rPython
Imports: AnnotationDbi,genefilter,statmod
Suggests: org.Mm.eg.db, org.Hs.eg.db,DESeq2,ggplot2
